comments.body:
Graceful degradation is great, and I see your argument for applying it here. But if a system operator (or automation) can't tell that it has happened, then they have no way to decide whether they want to make a remediation to the system to fix it and get the system back into a non-degraded mode. 

Is the fallback from iptables --> user mode discoverable in any way?

